  "body": "The demo function from this page:\r\n\r\nhttps://docs.openzeppelin.com/contracts/4.x/utilities#api:cryptography.adoc#ECDSA\r\n\r\nusing this code:\r\n\r\n```\r\nimport \"@openzeppelin/contracts/utils/cryptography/ECDSA.sol\";\r\n...\r\n\r\nusing ECDSA for bytes32;\r\n\r\nfunction _verify(bytes32 data, address account, bytes32 signature) pure public returns (bool) {\r\n        return keccak256(data)\r\n            .toEthSignedMessageHash()\r\n            .recover(signature) == account;\r\n    }\r\n```\r\n\r\nFails with this error:\r\n\r\n```\r\nTypeError: Member \"recover\" not found or not visible after argument-dependent lookup in bytes32.\r\n  --> contracts/...:51:16:\r\n   |\r\n51 |         return keccak256(data)\r\n   |                ^ (Relevant source part starts here and spans across multiple lines).\r\n```\r\n\r\nI just added the signature to the _verify parameters and public otherwise it wouldn't work. I'm using \r\n\"@openzeppelin/contracts\": \"^4.0.0\",",
